===Etymology===
From {{It.}} ''[[caffè]]'' < {{Turk.}} ''[[kahve]]'' < {{Arab.}} {{ARchar|[[قهوة]]}} (qahwa) ‘coffee’ < [[w:Kaffa|Kaffa]], an ancient province of Ethiopia where coffee is said to have originated.
*Some sources state that the Arabic term also meant ‘wine’.

===Pronunciation===
*(US) {{IPA|/ˈkɑfi/}}
*{{audio|en-us-coffee.ogg|Audio (US)}}
:* Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɒfi|-ɒfi]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun|-}}

# A [[beverage]] made by [[infuse|infusing]] the [[bean]]s of the coffee plant in hot water.
# The seeds of the plant used to make coffee, misnamed ‘beans’ due to their shape.
# A [[tropical]] [[plant]] of the genus ''[[Coffea]]''.
# {{italbrac|colour}} A pale brown colour, like that of milk coffee.
